      {
        "id": "983420c0a3d3c96ca9e43b830f8694bc72ea284e",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 57,
          "name": "Pamela Dragosh",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "pd1248@att.com",
          "username": "pdragosh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-01-17 13:15:58.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nOk this was put it so the latest Jackson could be used and remove older version being used. (BTW I will be updating the XACML PDP to remove jackson also). Is this needed to be put back in because JVM now cannot find jackson for XACML to use?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "c37da2e9735aeb25df26191f206590e23b5559c4",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 811,
          "name": "Jim Hahn",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jrh3@att.com",
          "username": "jrh3"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-01-17 14:51:17.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Ok this was put it so the latest Jackson could be used and remove\n > older version being used. (BTW I will be updating the XACML PDP to\n > remove jackson also). Is this needed to be put back in because JVM\n > now cannot find jackson for XACML to use?\n\nNot sure I fully understand the comment.  From the mvn dependency tree, it does not appear that \"xacml-pdp\" uses jackson directly, while \n\"xacml\" does reference jackson.  This runs in a standalone install, so didn't think jackson was really needed, particularly since the code does not serialize/deserialize any of the xacml data structures.  Nevertheless, may it's happy because it's still getting jackson due to policy-endpoints or policy-management.\nSo, I can leave this change in for now, and fix things later once jackson is removed from policy-endpoints and policy-management, or I can abandon this change, since the reference is indirect, and address it later.  Your call.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "6c90d3d891bbffa115d322962c4d89f89e6652cf",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 57,
          "name": "Pamela Dragosh",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "pd1248@att.com",
          "username": "pdragosh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-01-17 16:35:37.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nYes the xacml-pdp does use jackson directly, but it was an older version. We upgraded and at least at that time cleared the security issue. Of course now the security is for every version so it doesn't matter. If jackson is ultimately removed from all the policy/drools-applications, then this review is necessary.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
